messages.message: We were playing around with a refiner with C1 and trying to use `nlp_token_find`, but it looks like they don’t have some/any of the matchers we have on .com. They’re on the October release… are these matchers newer than that? If not, how do they get them?
Do you happen to know the exact function they’re using? There’s a possibility you need to format the model differently. The syntax for the nlp functions is a bit funky @Felicia
Also possible that those matchers didn’t exist yet in the october release
Hmm got it. This is working on dogfood and .com so maybe they don’t have the matchers at all
i’m not sure when exactly the october release went out but i see a bunch of PRs related to addresses from aug to november 2019
so could be it didn’t make it in
Their use case isn’t too crazy (unpacking a North American address) so we can take a different approach for now. Who would have the most context around which version would have these?
